      Information



      General Information
      Blackmores Colon Care is a pleasant tasting mild laxative, prepared with fibre and herbs proven to gently assist cleansing of the bowel and functioning of the colon. Colon Care promotes elimination and rids the body of waste.To improve bowel function we recommend that plenty of water and fibre be included in the diet.The laxative herbs in this formula (Senna and Buckthorn) contain anthraquinone glycosides which stimulate peristalsis of the bowel wall stimulating evacuation, (normally around 8 hours after intake). Psyllium, Irish Moss and Agar are sources of soluble and insoluble fibres to facilitate natural bowel movements.Aniseed and Liquorice root are carminative herbs that are helpful to relieve the discomfort associated with constipation and to prevent the griping pain that is often associated with laxative use. Irish moss and Agar are demulcents which soothe inflamed gastric mucosa.


      Miscellaneous



      Drug Interactions



      Warnings
      Not recommended for children under 12 years. Prolonged use of laxatives may cause serious bowel problems. Do not use when abdominal pain, nausea or vomiting are present, or if you develop diarrhoea. If digestive symptoms persist, see your healthcare practitioner.

Do not use during pregnancy or breast feeding.


      Common Uses



      Ingredients
      Active ingredients per gram:
Senna leaf dry 500mg;
Rhamnus catharticus (Buckthorn) bark dry 250mg;
Psyllium husk powder 80mg;
Psyllium seed dry 50mg;
Aniseed powder 40mg;
Foeniculm vulgrare (fennel) seed powder 40mg;
Glycyrrhiza glabra (Liquorice) root powder 10mg;
Arctostaphylos uva-ursi(Uva ursi)leaf powder 10mg;
Chondrus crispus (Irish Moss) plant powder 10mg;
Agar 10mg.


      Directions
      Adults:
Place 1 to 3g (one half to one level metric teaspoon) on the tongue followed by a full glass of water. Add to fresh or stewed fruit, cereals, soups or vegetables. As a tea, add 3g (one level metric teaspoon) to 1 cup of boiling water, steep for 10 minutes, strain and drink. Best taken last thing at night, before retiring.


      Indications


      Information



      General Information
      Blackmores Men's Performance MultiSpecifically formulated to help men perform in peak condition physically and mentally:* B vitamins for energy support;* zinc for healthy immune and reproductive systems, and production of healthy sperm;* Tribulus, traditionally used to assist male sexual performance;* Damiana to support testosterone levels, improve male stamina and relieve stress and anxiety;* antioxidants to reduce risk of cell damage due to stress, poor diet and lifestyle.* ginkgo traditionally used for circulation to extremities;* milk thistle to support liver detoxification.The unique blend of herbs provides reproductive support and performance, along with detoxification and stress lowering.The B group vitamins together with minerals help to correct any underlying nutritional deficiencies. B group vitamins assist nervous system function and are beneficial at times of increased physical and mental demand.Zinc is crucial for the production of healthy sperm. It is also an antioxidant which helps to protect against free radical damage.Selenium is another potent antioxidant with its highest concentration among the reproductive organs being the testes.Tribulus, damiana, and ginkgo are all herbs traditionally offering benefits to the male reproductive system.Tribulus has been traditionally used to enhance male stamina and performance. Damiana traditionally helps with male performance, particularly where anxiety is involved. Milk thistle is a liver detoxifying herb that helps to regenerate liver tissue. It is particularly useful when living a busy lifestyle that involves coffee, alcohol, and exposure to other toxins. It helps to enhance the body’s detoxification enzyme systems.Ginkgo biloba is an antioxidant herb that improves circulation to the extremities.


      Miscellaneous



      Drug Interactions



      Warnings
      Not suitable for children under 15 years. Selenium is toxic in high doses. Selenium in dietary supplements should not exceed a daily dose of 100mcg.


